    <text>
        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>316 Leigh St<lb/>
                Richmond Va<lb/>
                Octr 22. 78<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev S Morais<lb/>
                My dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>Not having heard yet&#44;<lb/> from you about Luzzatos<lb/> Isaiah I presume you have<lb/> not received it so far.<lb/>  I have been installed here as<lb/> minister in the German Congn<lb/> for the last two months&#45;&#45;<lb/> My congn is quite large altho&#39;<lb/> there are many in humble cir&#45;<lb/>cumstances&#44; the wealthy are<lb/> &#91;Hebrew&#93;&#45;&#45;I have furnished a<lb/> neat little house &#38; have thus<lb/> two of the things &#91;Hebrew&#93;<lb/> &#91;Hebrew&#93;<lb/> Rev Mr Chumaceiro officiated<lb/> in the Portuguese &#38; gave general<lb/> satisfaction&#45;&#45;<lb/></p>
            <p>He told me he preaches extempore<lb/> without preparation I think<lb/> neither you nor I can say<lb/> as much<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>I have to work hard&#45;&#45;<lb/> I was expected to preach<lb/> twice New Year three times<lb/> on day of Atonement<lb/> The climate here is very much<lb/> to my taste &#38; I am glad<lb/> I came here<lb/></p>
            <p>I hope you are well &#38;<lb/> that you passed the holiday<lb/> very pleasantly &#38; that<lb/> you&#44; &#38; yours &#91;Hebrew&#93; were<lb/> inscribed &#91;Hebrew&#93;<lb/> &#91;Hebrew&#93;<lb/></p>
            <p>I am<lb/>
                Yours Obedtly<lb/>
                A Harris<lb/></p>
            <p>P.S<lb/>
                Among the applicants<lb/> for my position was<lb/> Rev Elkin of your city<lb/> he stated frankly that he<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>had been in the receipt of<lb/> &#36;3000 that his salary<lb/> was reduced to &#36;2000 &#38;<lb/> that he was desirous of<lb/> bettering himself<lb/></p>
        </body>
